<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 1:09PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of east central Judith
Basin and south central Fergus Counties through 145 PM MDT...
At 109 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles southwest of Moore, or 20 miles southwest of Lewistown, moving
east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of east central Judith
Basin and south central Fergus Counties.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
